I could sell her for 40.

280
00:18:58,001 --> 00:19:02,991
Aye, but when've late life medical bills been cheap?

281
00:19:03,041 --> 00:19:04,462
Late life?

282
00:19:04,551 --> 00:19:06,372
Medical bills?

283
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:08,778
Watch what you're saying!

284
00:19:08,778 --> 00:19:10,878
Watch what <i>you</i>'re sayin'!

285
00:19:10,878 --> 00:19:12,728
I say,

286
00:19:12,728 --> 00:19:13,929
Take your 40.

287
00:19:13,929 --> 00:19:15,410
Don't spend 70!

288
00:19:15,447 --> 00:19:16,529
And...

289
00:19:16,529 --> 00:19:20,370
You can think of her as your lover all you want,

290
00:19:20,430 --> 00:19:22,138
But she can't go on!

291
00:19:22,138 --> 00:19:24,892
'Bout time you found someone else!

292
00:19:25,058 --> 00:19:29,048
In fact, if you can afford it,

293
00:19:29,118 --> 00:19:34,320
Sell her, add some o' your savings, and get a motorcycle. So much the better!

294
00:19:34,370 --> 00:19:37,060
How dare you --
-Hey!
-What d'you think you're doing?

295
00:19:37,060 --> 00:19:39,819
You heard what he said!

296
00:19:39,980 --> 00:19:41,731
He's right.

297
00:19:42,359 --> 00:19:49,390
Actually, you can't even get a bike with that money. Get a bicycle. Or better yet, a tricycle!

298
00:20:03,330 --> 00:20:06,047
So you actually slapped her?

299
00:20:06,278 --> 00:20:09,268
Four years ago! Can't believe she's still furious!

300
00:20:09,329 --> 00:20:11,873
Governments change twice in four years here.

301
00:20:11,873 --> 00:20:13,413
But...

302
00:20:13,883 --> 00:20:17,883
There's an ocean of difference between governments and hearts, laddie...

303
00:20:17,883 --> 00:20:19,403
Honestly?

304
00:20:21,254 --> 00:20:23,024
She's mad.

305
00:20:23,060 --> 00:20:25,599
Get her treated!

306
00:20:27,691 --> 00:20:31,171
Not like you're any better...

307
00:20:31,231 --> 00:20:33,891
Who's gonna treat you?

308
00:20:35,221 --> 00:20:36,792
Know what,

309
00:20:37,832 --> 00:20:40,332
If I didn't slap her that day,

310
00:20:40,361 --> 00:20:42,741
The four of us would've been arrested!

311
00:20:42,802 --> 00:20:44,522
Know what she was up to?

312
00:20:44,522 --> 00:20:46,933
Forget it, mate...

313
00:20:47,212 --> 00:20:48,822
What?

314
00:20:48,873 --> 00:20:52,510
None of your concern.

315
00:20:52,950 --> 00:20:55,118
She's just a girl...

316
00:20:55,145 --> 00:20:58,988
I'm sure she was up to her tricks, as always...

317
00:20:59,082 --> 00:21:02,913
Tricks! That's like a massive understatement... And -- Aunt...

318
00:21:02,913 --> 00:21:04,274
Hmm!

319
00:21:05,480 --> 00:21:08,398
Can't you mind your tongue?

320
00:21:09,790 --> 00:21:11,133
Go...

321
00:21:11,428 --> 00:21:13,629
Say sorry to her.

322
00:21:15,350 --> 00:21:16,750
Say what?

323
00:21:16,750 --> 00:21:18,528
Say sorry...

324
00:21:18,578 --> 00:21:21,238
It's best for you.

325
00:21:21,700 --> 00:21:26,499
Or you won't find life easy in Karachi.

326
00:21:27,219 --> 00:21:28,798
You threatening me?

327
00:21:28,843 --> 00:21:30,680
No, m'lad...

328
00:21:30,680 --> 00:21:33,091
I just want to say...

329
00:21:33,160 --> 00:21:36,740
Bowing down for a moment ain't gonna hurt you...

330
00:21:36,740 --> 00:21:39,609
But it'll sure calm her down...

331
00:21:40,620 --> 00:21:42,620
Say sorry? To that imp?

332
00:21:42,650 --> 00:21:45,830
If I bow down, she won't let me get back up, like ever!

333
00:21:45,850 --> 00:21:49,168
As if she'd let you if you don't!

334
00:21:50,320 --> 00:21:55,038
You're going too far up and away, boy... It's a long way down.

335
00:21:55,098 --> 00:21:57,468
Dado's right.

336
00:21:58,739 --> 00:22:00,258
Can it...

337
00:22:01,640 --> 00:22:03,948
I'm never saying sorry.

338
00:22:04,788 --> 00:22:07,498
I'm never bowing down before her.

339
00:22:07,531 --> 00:22:09,068
Okay...

340
00:22:09,118 --> 00:22:12,248
Have it your way...

341
00:22:12,318 --> 00:22:15,088
Do something that says it for you.

342
00:22:15,210 --> 00:22:16,490
Such as?

343
00:22:16,490 --> 00:22:17,978
Blimey...

344
00:22:18,828 --> 00:22:21,338
Do I really have to tell you?

345
00:22:21,509 --> 00:22:23,890
Don't you live in London?

346
00:22:23,950 --> 00:22:27,781
Don't you gad about, don't you see the ladies?

347
00:22:27,816 --> 00:22:30,936
Learnt anything from all of that?

348
00:22:33,730 --> 00:22:36,218
Ali... Tell him, will you?

349
00:22:36,218 --> 00:22:37,848
No need...

350
00:22:37,876 --> 00:22:39,530
You said it.

351
00:22:39,530 --> 00:22:40,838
I'll say it...

352
00:22:40,838 --> 00:22:43,999
'It was just a slap! Big deal'!

353
00:22:45,218 --> 00:22:47,829
So... Where's her room?

354
00:22:49,520 --> 00:22:52,320
Goodness knows who she thinks she is!

355
00:22:58,630 --> 00:23:00,231
Poor lad...

356
00:23:22,180 --> 00:23:23,928
Not so fast!

357
00:23:24,478 --> 00:23:26,968
If you knock, she's gonna ask who it is.

358
00:23:26,968 --> 00:23:28,280
I'll say, 'It's me'.

359
00:23:28,280 --> 00:23:30,903
She ain't opening the door if it's you!

360
00:23:32,780 --> 00:23:33,338
So?

361
00:23:33,338 --> 00:23:36,579
I'll say 'It's me'.

362
00:23:38,058 --> 00:23:39,498
I guess I'd better apologise.

363
00:23:39,498 --> 00:23:41,839
And lose every ounce of respect here.

364
00:23:41,839 --> 00:23:44,870
As if I'd be any better if I knocked!

365
00:23:46,900 --> 00:23:48,464
Anyway --

366
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:02,331
<i>You</i>!

367
00:24:02,390 --> 00:24:05,040
Right outside my room?

368
00:24:05,258 --> 00:24:05,851
How.

369
00:24:05,851 --> 00:24:06,110
How. Dare.

370
00:24:06,110 --> 00:24:07,670
How. Dare. You!?

371
00:24:07,705 --> 00:24:10,105
Don't speak English. Dado's downstairs.

372
00:24:10,155 --> 00:24:12,055
Why are you here?

373
00:24:12,156 --> 00:24:14,396
Thought I'd make peace.

374
00:24:14,710 --> 00:24:16,109
Wow!

375
00:24:16,460 --> 00:24:21,170
Dado wants me to forget everything. I thought that to forget everything, I should remember my fault.

376
00:24:21,170 --> 00:24:22,040
You!

377
00:24:22,040 --> 00:24:22,680
You! Get.

378
00:24:22,680 --> 00:24:23,548
You! Get. Lost!

379
00:24:23,548 --> 00:24:26,918
Forget making peace... Or forgiveness!

380
00:24:26,968 --> 00:24:27,878
Aye,

381
00:24:27,878 --> 00:24:29,348
There's one way...

382
00:24:29,348 --> 00:24:31,888
To make peace and forgive you...

383
00:24:31,935 --> 00:24:33,825
We're all ears...

384
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:36,859
How 'bout I

385
00:24:36,859 --> 00:24:37,838
Give him

386
00:24:37,838 --> 00:24:40,310
A proper slap? Just like his!
-Hey!

387
00:24:40,330 --> 00:24:42,470
She's given you her word.

388
00:24:42,470 --> 00:24:45,478
Blimey, Maheen, that slap was real bad...

389
00:24:45,528 --> 00:24:47,068
I was right about you.

390
00:24:47,068 --> 00:24:48,410
Absolutely right.

391
00:24:48,410 --> 00:24:49,440
What?

392
00:24:49,440 --> 00:24:54,818
You've got a screw loose! You're barking mad! Occasionally sane, and frequently insane!

393
00:24:54,868 --> 00:24:55,850
You actually said that?

394
00:24:55,850 --> 00:24:59,708
Oh, I wanted to say a lot more, but Dado ordered me to make peace, so I came here.

395
00:24:59,769 --> 00:25:00,269
Im-

396
00:25:00,269 --> 00:25:01,960
Im-POSSIBLE!

397
00:25:10,620 --> 00:25:12,958
Back to work, everyone...

398
00:25:12,958 --> 00:25:14,477
C'mon.

399
00:25:15,210 --> 00:25:19,340
C'mon, folks... Guess we're just wastin' time here.

400
00:25:25,450 --> 00:25:27,618
Peace be upon you.

401
00:25:27,738 --> 00:25:29,208
And upon you, peace.

402
00:25:29,208 --> 00:25:31,571
Where were you all day?

403
00:25:34,120 --> 00:25:35,818
With Foxy.

404
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:38,477
Wonder who that is.

405
00:25:38,568 --> 00:25:40,450
Gulrez's car.

406
00:25:40,500 --> 00:25:42,738
But you've got your own car.

407
00:25:42,819 --> 00:25:44,660
Aye, but

408
00:25:45,219 --> 00:25:48,460
I had to tow his Foxy

409
00:25:48,710 --> 00:25:50,340
To the workshop.

410
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:51,990
Jesus Christ...

411
00:25:52,060 --> 00:25:54,529
When will he see sense?

412
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:59,030
I guess there's only one way.

413
00:25:59,071 --> 00:26:00,641
Yeah?

414
00:26:01,241 --> 00:26:04,648
Ask Maheen she'd better not

415
00:26:04,862 --> 00:26:06,203
Accept the proposal

416
00:26:06,203 --> 00:26:08,111
While the Foxy lives.

417
00:26:08,111 --> 00:26:10,315
What d'you mean, lives?

418
00:26:10,760 --> 00:26:14,259
He's betting 70 gee on that geriatric rust bucket.

419
00:26:14,359 --> 00:26:17,521
He'd do anything to keep her alive.

420
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:19,699
Come here, mate...

421
00:26:24,960 --> 00:26:26,158
Here.

422
00:26:27,168 --> 00:26:30,127
Our profits have gone up 11% since last month.

423
00:26:30,127 --> 00:26:31,498
Wow...

424
00:26:31,637 --> 00:26:33,330
Congratulations.

425
00:26:34,740 --> 00:26:36,426
We've hit all our targets

426
00:26:36,426 --> 00:26:38,937
And production goals on time.

427
00:26:39,177 --> 00:26:41,418
And you know who did it.

428
00:26:41,698 --> 00:26:42,740
Not me and you.

429
00:26:42,740 --> 00:26:44,329
It's Gulrez.

430
00:26:44,550 --> 00:26:45,958
Wow...

431
00:26:47,120 --> 00:26:48,377
Hmm!

432
00:26:49,197 --> 00:26:50,828
So...

433
00:26:51,288 --> 00:26:53,098
What d'you think?

434
00:26:53,159 --> 00:26:55,847
D'you think... When she's done 'thinking'...

435
00:26:55,894 --> 00:26:57,238
She'd agree?

436
00:26:57,238 --> 00:26:58,500
Honestly?

437
00:26:58,500 --> 00:26:59,659
No idea.

438
00:26:59,659 --> 00:27:01,519
How'd I know?

439
00:27:01,820 --> 00:27:05,666
I just know she wants some time to think.

440
00:27:05,724 --> 00:27:08,925
Neelam says it's perfectly fine.

441
00:27:10,650 --> 00:27:12,488
What d'you say?

442
00:27:13,788 --> 00:27:15,348
No idea.

443
00:27:15,398 --> 00:27:17,429
But aye, Ammi Begum said

444
00:27:17,491 --> 00:27:19,322
It's nothing to worry about.

445
00:27:19,371 --> 00:27:21,581
Then why are you so worried?

446
00:27:22,551 --> 00:27:26,301
I'm sure she just wants to give Gulrez the frights.

447
00:27:27,112 --> 00:27:30,061
Looking at Gulrez, you can't exactly fault her.

448
00:27:31,092 --> 00:27:33,353
I think she'd agree

449
00:27:33,432 --> 00:27:35,933
After she's done playing with him.

450
00:27:37,242 --> 00:27:38,033
Hmm...

451
00:27:38,033 --> 00:27:39,823
May God will thus.

452
00:27:39,933 --> 00:27:41,344
Tea?

453
00:27:41,520 --> 00:27:42,899
Sure.

454
00:27:45,690 --> 00:27:46,978
No.

455
00:27:47,148 --> 00:27:49,998
No way we can make peace until Doomsday.

456
00:27:50,058 --> 00:27:55,018
Who'd want to make peace with that ham-fisted, insolent, arrogant girl?

457
00:27:55,298 --> 00:27:57,818
She hasn't got an ounce of decency in her!

458
00:27:57,879 --> 00:27:59,159
I mean --

459
00:27:59,249 --> 00:28:01,969
Imagine you're back from England after four long years,

460
00:28:01,969 --> 00:28:04,479
And go to your cousin's to see her,

461
00:28:04,540 --> 00:28:08,481
Only to find out the lady left a birthday party because of shock over some engagement foul-up,

462
00:28:08,561 --> 00:28:13,141
And be welcomed as a runagate when you finally see her!

463
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:16,207
Suddenly, she remembers an old slap,

464
00:28:16,207 --> 00:28:17,958
And, when you try to make peace,

465
00:28:17,958 --> 00:28:20,798
Shuts the door in your face!

466
00:28:24,160 --> 00:28:29,068
Tell me - would either of you ever want to see her face again?

467
00:28:32,070 --> 00:28:33,812
No, yes?

468
00:28:34,718 --> 00:28:35,668
Yes!

469
00:28:35,668 --> 00:28:37,208
That's what I think too.

470
00:28:37,249 --> 00:28:38,998
We didn't say a word.

471
00:28:38,998 --> 00:28:41,010
That's what your silence said.

472
00:28:41,010 --> 00:28:44,650
No. Our silence means you're plain wrong.

473
00:28:44,650 --> 00:28:46,008
Yes!

474
00:28:46,598 --> 00:28:48,258
You're all in it together.

475
00:28:48,258 --> 00:28:51,859
Partly, you're right. We took an oath. Pledged our allegiance.

476
00:28:51,859 --> 00:28:53,499
Ooh...

477
00:28:53,948 --> 00:28:56,859
Now I know who's inflaming her.

478
00:28:56,950 --> 00:28:59,290
She's just asking for her right.

479
00:28:59,290 --> 00:29:02,651
Which you violated so unashamedly with that slap.

480
00:29:02,678 --> 00:29:03,631
Ooh.

481
00:29:03,675 --> 00:29:08,290
If you just said a simple sorry instead of that 'ooh', I'm sure she'd forgive you.

482
00:29:08,290 --> 00:29:09,440
Wow...

483
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:12,207
The words we recommend to you are the simple...

484
00:29:12,207 --> 00:29:12,638
'I

485
00:29:12,638 --> 00:29:13,038
'I am

486
00:29:13,038 --> 00:29:14,059
'I am sorry'!

487
00:29:14,059 --> 00:29:14,648
Shut.

488
00:29:14,648 --> 00:29:15,599
Shut. Up!

489
00:29:15,599 --> 00:29:17,678
That adds fuel to the fire!

490
00:29:17,728 --> 00:29:19,229
I don't care.

491
00:29:19,309 --> 00:29:21,940
You have to, Waqar Ahmed. She's my sister.

492
00:29:21,940 --> 00:29:23,671
And I'm an eyewitness.

493
00:29:23,671 --> 00:29:26,900
I've seen her cry for hours over that slap.

494
00:29:26,900 --> 00:29:29,014
But it's your choice...

495
00:29:29,700 --> 00:29:30,200
C'mon!

496
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:31,618
Ju -- Just a sec! Hey!

497
00:29:31,618 --> 00:29:33,158
On your feet!

498
00:29:34,330 --> 00:29:36,140
And I'm an eyewitness.

499
00:29:36,140 --> 00:29:39,848
I've seen her cry for hours over that slap.

500
00:30:10,040 --> 00:30:12,318
What does the doctor say?

501
00:30:14,410 --> 00:30:16,827
I mean, the mechanic...

502
00:30:18,020 --> 00:30:20,048
Don't even mention him.

503
00:30:20,128 --> 00:30:22,850
I haven't seen such a cheap man!

504
00:30:23,719 --> 00:30:25,741
Wali told me everything.

505
00:30:25,783 --> 00:30:28,010
She can't be fixed!

506
00:30:28,040 --> 00:30:29,468
I know.

507
00:30:29,518 --> 00:30:32,049
Then could you please leave this -- Funeral?

508
00:30:32,093 --> 00:30:34,728
I was thinking about the palmist.

509
00:30:35,209 --> 00:30:37,479
You saw a palmist?

510
00:30:37,849 --> 00:30:39,989
Doesn't make much of a difference, that.

511
00:30:39,989 --> 00:30:41,210
What?

512
00:30:41,270 --> 00:30:44,130
That man was more of a mechanic.

513
00:30:44,164 --> 00:30:47,035
I'm sure he told you it's her time.

514
00:30:47,073 --> 00:30:50,600
He said my fate is inseparable from hers.

515
00:30:50,730 --> 00:30:53,809
As in, he wants you to keep it with you?

516
00:30:54,080 --> 00:30:55,438
No.

517
00:30:55,528 --> 00:30:58,048
He wants me to sell her,

518
00:31:00,269 --> 00:31:03,919
Or, he says, my life would be at a dead end. Like her.

519
00:31:05,010 --> 00:31:07,319
He's got a point, Neelam...

520
00:31:08,010 --> 00:31:12,428
When she heard about the engagement, she was drained of all cheer.

521
00:31:13,670 --> 00:31:16,072
Almost felt like... She'd refuse...

522
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:19,638
She said she needed some time to think...

523
00:31:20,519 --> 00:31:23,808
I'm at a dead end, so to speak...

524
00:31:26,120 --> 00:31:28,688
Who knows how long she needs...

525
00:31:30,598 --> 00:31:34,068
And how long I need to decide whether to sell this Foxy

526
00:31:34,112 --> 00:31:36,572
Or spend 70 gee on her...

527
00:31:42,900 --> 00:31:47,278
If you ask me... Even if she won't move an inch now...

528
00:31:48,288 --> 00:31:52,038
I can't forget how she's stood by me all these years.

529
00:31:56,150 --> 00:31:58,208
I haven't had anything all day.

530
00:31:59,120 --> 00:32:03,408
Looking at her dying old face kills my hunger.

531
00:32:05,620 --> 00:32:07,618
Come in for lunch?

532
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:11,011
Blimey, Neelam... Don't you get it?

533
00:32:11,280 --> 00:32:14,918
I'm asking you if I should spend 70 gee on her.

534
00:32:17,100 --> 00:32:18,998
I don't see why not.

535
00:32:30,660 --> 00:32:32,298
Aye, Wali...

536
00:32:39,590 --> 00:32:41,269
What is it?

537
00:32:43,170 --> 00:32:45,498
I'm very upset.

538
00:32:48,300 --> 00:32:50,260
Aren't we all?

539
00:32:50,890 --> 00:32:53,072
What happened?

540
00:32:55,010 --> 00:32:56,748
It's simple.

541
00:32:57,167 --> 00:32:59,228
It's so simple.

542
00:33:00,588 --> 00:33:03,228
He'd die without Maheen.

543
00:33:17,190 --> 00:33:20,110
I thought I'd remind you...

544
00:33:20,644 --> 00:33:24,575
Our family's borne too many palls already.

545
00:33:25,850 --> 00:33:28,348
That was an accident.

546
00:33:33,720 --> 00:33:36,261
But this time,

547
00:33:36,451 --> 00:33:38,561
The death

548
00:33:39,110 --> 00:33:41,781
Would be our doing.

549
00:34:23,360 --> 00:34:24,867
Hello?

550
00:34:26,368 --> 00:34:27,868
Hello!

551
00:34:29,357 --> 00:34:30,397
Who is it?

552
00:34:30,397 --> 00:34:33,218
I thought you'd recognise my voice.

553
00:34:33,610 --> 00:34:35,293
Your voice

554
00:34:35,293 --> 00:34:37,314
Sounds familiar.

555
00:34:38,535 --> 00:34:41,815
You sound like my dirty rotten cousin.

556
00:34:41,861 --> 00:34:43,836
Who are you?

